%% Diagram: Undo with concurrent remote ops — invert + transform
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User A (editor)
    participant L as Local undo stack
    participant S as Server
    participant R as Remote clients

    Note over U,R: Doc at rev 10
    U->>S: opA — insert "foo" at 100 (baseRev 10)
    S->>S: apply, rev 11
    S->>U: ack (rev 11)
    U->>L: push inverse(opA) = delete(100..103) at rev 11

    Note over R,S: Concurrent remote work
    R->>S: opR1 — insert "X" at 50 (baseRev 11)
    S->>S: apply, rev 12
    S->>U: opR1 (rev 12)
    R->>S: opR2 — delete(80..82) (baseRev 12)
    S->>S: apply, rev 13
    S->>U: opR2 (rev 13)

    Note over U: User hits Ctrl-Z at rev 13
    U->>L: pop inverse(opA)
    U->>U: transform inverse(opA) against opR1, opR2<br/>→ inv_opA_prime = delete(101..104)
    U->>S: send inv_opA_prime (baseRev 13)
    S->>S: apply, rev 14
    S->>U: ack (rev 14)
    S->>R: broadcast inv_opA_prime (rev 14)
    Note over U,R: Converged: foo removed and opR1 opR2 preserved
